The paper deals with deep learning techniques for chest X-ray classification, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The use of ResNet-50, transfer learning, and fine-tuning are all common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The inclusion of patient age, gender, and acquisition type in the classification process suggests a potential application in medical informatics (cs.MED). Finally, the evaluation of the classifiers using ROC statistics and rank correlation is a common approach in information retrieval (cs.IR).
